In the legislation of J ustinian the rules respecting litis aestimatio were of less importanee, because the condemnatio was in many cases. no longer pecuniary but commanded the conveyance of property (dare), delivery of possession (tradere), restitution (restituere), or production (exhibere), of the specific thing itself that was the original subject of litigation.
